ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Recent pain in wrist or any acute flare up in hand or wrist from conditions like arthritis, tendonitis or carpal tunnel syndrome?
Notes: 1= Right hand or arm; 2= Left hand or arm; 3= Both hands or arms

ElementDescription: Surgery on hand or arms in the last 3 months?
Notes: 1= Right hand or arm; 2= Left hand or arm; 3= Both hands or arms

Does the participant use an assistive device for walking? If the response is "YES," please record the type of assistive device used.
Notes: 0= No assistive device; 1= Wheelchair; 2= Walker; 3= Quad/tripod cane; 4= Crutches; 5= Standard cane; 6= White cane (has red band at the bottom, used by visually impaired persons); 7= Other (specify)

I felt that everything I did was an effort.
Notes: 0 = Rarely or none of the time (less than 1 day); 1 = Some or a little of the time (1-2 days); 2 = Occasionally or a moderate amount of time (3-4 days); 3 = Most or all of the time (5-7 days); 99 = Prefer not to answer; 999= NA/NK/missing

ElementDescription: I could not get "going".
Notes: 0 = Rarely or none of the time (less than 1 day); 1 = Some or a little of the time (1-2 days); 2 = Occasionally or a moderate amount of time (3-4 days); 3 = Most or all of the time (5-7 days); 4 = Nearly every day for 2 weeks; 99 = Prefer not to answer; 999= NA/NK/missing; 888 = Skipped ; 777 = Condition Skipped ; 555 = Missing
